{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"764740fa-6330-4919-ad6f-ec9716ca0f6d","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFix: reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_e8HpD9SZQusWHhhbnRwpZr","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-64e0a4641d1d449f96927aebd38cae35/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-64e0a4641d1d449f96927aebd38cae35/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"02b9b74d-5879-463e-a697-2719f4fca80c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines `Domain` module\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — opens both\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the project file. The fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":464,"requestId":"282E:E9FEE:1BE3ADF:1EEDFF1:69FA8F7D"},"id":"abc01c32-ee64-42de-858e-68f5c70ddde9","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:47:01.400Z","parentId":"ee8e526b-01d5-4493-9191-009473e51e76"}
